Always use strict TypeScript.
Prefer small functions with explicit return types.
Use React Server Components in web routes unless client interactivity is required.
Do not add new dependencies without a written reason.
Never expose internal database types in public API responses.
Run the package check before proposing a commit.
Keep generated files out of source control.
Prefer accessibility-first UI primitives.
Document security-sensitive changes in the pull request.
Avoid broad refactors during focused bug fixes.
